snippet.textDisplay:
Awesome video. Send it to everyone!

On a side note: as someone with 6+ chronic autoimmune diseases plus being on immunosuppressant medications, I saw this coming (the spreading) BUT I spend my life thinking about germs and stress and weakened immune systems, so I'm more hypervigilant about that.

People, especially healthy people, they just don't think about germs, viruses, bacteria and how it spreads. The tiny impossible to see organisms that are alive are just everywhere and you can think you're protecting yourself, but these tiny bastards, they find that one tiny hole in your mask, your gloves, your skin, your whatever and they go to town, breeding.

I already stay in my home, with so many health issues and chronic pain, I really only leave my house for doctor appointments, average 3x a month. I take my precautions. But I have another body, a family member, who lives with me, who goes out into the world for 8-10 hours a day, 5 days a week. Prior to this, she's vigilant about staying healthy, gets her vaccines, pays attention to coworkers who are sick. But those damn germs, they find their way into the home.

So now with this, the way it spreads, it's amazing (if I can use that term without being offensive). For me, it's not how fast it's spreading, it's that people have it, are asymptomatic and passing it without even knowing. Thousands, if not millions, have this and don't even know. They may get sick but it'll be mild because their body and immune system are top notch. But then there are the elderly and people like me, we won't survive this.

I've been sick got 25 years, I've accepted my own mortality and how I may die, but there are millions who just aren't ready to die. Please don't send them to their grave. Stay home!

snippet.textDisplay:
The virus can affect ANYBODY, the only difference is that the worst symptoms are more likely to appear in older people because their immune system is not as strong. But this doesn’t mean that younger people CAN’T have complications. They potentially can. And even if they don’t and the only symptoms are light fever or cough, they should try to stay home as much as possible in order to limit the spread of the virus.
This is the only way everyone can protect people with immunodeficiency, people who are under cancer treatments and therefore have a compromised immune system. We have to do this especially for them, and also to respect the work of doctors and nurses who are fighting constantly on the front lines to save lives. Every life counts. Please people, don’t be selfish and try to prevent the spreading. You can do it.
I also still hear people saying that Coronavirus is almost the same as flue. Well, it is not. If it complicates, it can affect directly the alveolus and create much worst respiratory conditions than normal flue. Not to mention that for seasonal flue we all have a pretty strong immunity which we obviously don’t have for this virus. That’s why it spreads so quickly.

I just hope we will all get trough this as soon as possible. Wish you all the best

From an Italian❤️

snippet.textDisplay:
I’m pissed.

I am currently living in Washington, literally the center of the virus in America right now. Other areas will get worse unfortunately, like Cali and new York and Florida. But now is now and Washington numbers are going to skyrocket

We aren’t doing enough and I really wish we were. Us as civilians can’t do anything to help others around us except stay hygienic and away from big crowds and prevent spread to the best of our abilities. I can’t provide anything to the medical communities except keep myself and others sick. I wish I could do more and help more, but I can’t.

People coming to the hospitals with mild symptoms are being rejected and are told they can’t be tested simply because the hospitals do not have enough testing kits. Things are already spiraling and I can see the numbers jumping exponentially in the next couple of days.

Of course my situation here is not as bad as other places, but it is only going to get worse. Schools have been postponed til April 24th. This is a six week break, literally three fourths of summer. This is a big deal, and I do not know why people aren’t treating it as such

I do not know much about politics and the politicians in charge, but things need to change. Things need to happen quickly. We are not prepared here. I don’t want to cause panic, but we are still so behind in where we should be regarding our preparedness.

I am angry and annoyed because America shouldn’t have pushed this to the back of our radar months ago. People in charge shouldn’t have said that this wasn’t a big deal.

To be honest, in all my life, I never imagined I’d be living in a time where an outbreak would happen. This whole thing feels surreal. And if I’m feeling this way, others must be too. Which means maybe some aren’t taking this seriously.

Which also means, when things get bad, we will not be prepared and we will not know what to do.

Please, everyone, take care of yourselves and those around you to the best of your abilities. Stay safe, and I hope to see everyone when this hopefully all blows over

Take care
